aming rule that says not to include a dollar sign ($) in test class names, which is confusing. \\n\\nI could create public helper classes nested within LauncherTest, ensuring the main method is designated as public static. From what I see, I can use reflection on these public nested classes effectively. Configuring runtime resources without hard-coding is a bit tricky, but it might be feasible by writing resource files dynamically.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering custom ClassLoader**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a custom ClassLoader that can return a ByteArrayInputStream for resource names, which might eliminate the need for test resources. This way, I could directly call mainWithExitCode, covering the getResourceAsStream functionality. \\n\\nI want to make sure that the dynamic class loading is properly supported, particularly for loading test nested app classes. Using ClassWorld to create a new realm with a context loader seems like the right approach, so I'll investigate how DefaultClassRealm loads classes based on the classloader passed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_THLMJlq8mCY1fUYcoXBse3rF|fc_027ebfea4c1e98ac0169f619f1d04081a0b22880b3cb9fc94d", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/classworlds/classworlds/1.1/main/extracted/org/codehaus/classworlds/DefaultClassRealm.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 580, "output": 1057, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18533, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777736157110, "responseId": "resp_027ebfea4c1e98ac0169f619dd736881a0b9c96bcd24fb1556"}}
